  "chapter": {
    "number": 13,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job Prepares His Case"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Indeed, my eyes have seen all this;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my ears have heard and understood.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you know, I also know;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I am not inferior to you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet I desire to speak to the Almighty",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and argue my case before God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You, however, smear with lies;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you are all worthless physicians.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If only you would remain silent;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for that would be your wisdom!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hear now my argument,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and listen to the plea of my lips.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Will you speak wickedly on God’s behalf",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or speak deceitfully for Him?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Would you show Him partiality",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or argue in His defense?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Would it be well when He examined you?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Could you deceive Him like a man?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely He would rebuke you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "if you secretly showed partiality.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Would His majesty not terrify you?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Would the dread of Him not fall upon you?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your maxims are proverbs of ashes;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your defenses are defenses of clay.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Be silent, and I will speak.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Then let come to me what may.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why do I put myself at risk",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3167
          },
          {
            "text": "and take my life in my own hands?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though He slay me, I will hope in Him.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3168
          },
          {
            "text": "I will still defend my ways to His face.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Moreover, this will be my salvation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for no godless man can appear before Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen carefully to my words;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let my declaration ring in your ears.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, now that I have prepared my case,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I know that I will be vindicated.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Can anyone indict me?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "If so, I will be silent and die.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Only grant these two things to me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that I need not hide from You:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Withdraw Your hand from me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and do not let Your terror frighten me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then call me, and I will answer,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or let me speak, and You can reply.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How many are my iniquities and sins?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Reveal to me my transgression and sin.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why do You hide Your face",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and consider me as Your enemy?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Would You frighten a windblown leaf?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Would You chase after dry chaff?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For You record bitter accusations against me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and bequeath to me the iniquities of my youth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You put my feet in the stocks",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and stand watch over all my paths;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You set a limit",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the soles of my feet.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So man wastes away like something rotten,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a moth-eaten garment.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 3167,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Literally Why do I take my flesh in my teeth",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 13,
          "verse": 14
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 3168,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or I have no other hope",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 13,
          "verse": 15
        }
      }
    ]
